HEADWORD: Swietenia
<hw>Swie*te"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. Named
after Gerard Van <ets>Sweiten</ets>, physician to Maria Theresa of
Austria.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of meliaceous trees
consisting of one species (<spn>Sweitenia Mahogoni</spn>), the mahogany
tree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

